pageContext.description: Simensions: EL 78.2mm; Wm 26mm; Bm 26.3mm; Ts (at break) 1.3-2.6mm,Typology: neat flat bottom to socket rim; decoration probably cast - band of 3 narrow ribs above mouth-moulding, central broader moulding with angled profile, band of 4 narrow ribs, grooves in between moudlings and defining upper limit of band; some variations in spacing, etc.,Manufacture: sub-rect. end to mouldings on socket sides - near flat surfaces,Condition: main fracture may be recent; rivet-holes much damaged, chip out of m., fine cracks in body - some possibly ancient; part broken off since early NBI entry,Attached Material: fawn-orange dust?
pageContext.surface: Dull green patina - slightly shiny; mainly edges deteriorating to pale green dry surface.
pageContext.site: Unprovenanced,Alt Site: Shropshire; Little Wenlock; Willowmoor; c. SJ 6403 0830
